Description. Thickly encrusting to massive (
Fig. 1
), thickness varying from a few millimeters to 25 mm , covering areas up to 100 cm ² . Surface smooth, entirely covered by pore-sieves, 1.5–2 mm in diameter. Oscules scattered, 2–3 mm in diameter in preserved specimens. Consistency fleshy, rather soft. Colour deep red in live specimens, cream in alcohol.
